Sunday September 1st 2013 12:50 pm -04:00,Hello again Anat. (I will answer to you in English so everyone with the same question can understand what Im saying.)See in theory or at least from what Ive understand for every exercise there are two deadlines: the standard one and the hard deadline. The first one is the time before you are expected to send your answers so the teachers can keep track of the progress of everyone. However since not everybody has the same agenda it is allowed to send the answers to the exercises or the assingments days after the first deadline without receiving a penalty. So after all you can submit it before the 9th and receive credit for it. The only difference (I think) is that you will be evaluated after the rest of the students just that.Ave!, Resolved,1
